        "body": "While preparing my GSoC proposal and setting up a local BHV prototype, I noticed the README describes what BHV does well but doesn't mention how to get a local dev environment running.\n\nFor someone coming in fresh, a few things weren't obvious:\n- Recommended Python version\n- Whether there's a preferred package manager / venv setup\n- The 'single command' startup that the README mentions — what does that look like in practice? Is it a Flask dev server for now, or is there a Makefile/Docker setup planned?\n- For the storage modes (local filesystem vs GitHub API-backed) — is there a recommended mode to start with for new contributors?\n\nA short `DEVELOPMENT.md` or even a `## Getting Started` section in the README would help new contributors orient faster. Happy to draft one if it would be useful — I already have a minimal working version locally so could document the path I took.\n\nTagging this as a question/suggestion, not a blocker.",
